title: C IN A NUTSHELL: THE DEFINITIVE REFERENCE
description: Author: Peter Prinz, Tony Crawford Edition: 2 edition Publication Date: December 26, 2015 Publisher: O`Reilly Media ISBN-10: 1491904755 ISBN-13: 978-1491904756 Pages: 824 pages Format: pdf Size: 9.0M --- The new edition of this classic O’Reilly reference provides clear, detailed explanations of every feature in the C language and runtime library, including multithreading, type-generic macros, and library functions that are new in the 2011 C standard (C11). If you want to understand the effects of an unfamiliar function, and how the standard library requires it to behave, you’ll find it here, along with a typical example. --- http://dlfeb.com/book/c-in-nutshell-definitive-reference/
